ection%20of%20analysts%20and%20overseas%20media%20reports%2C%20Israeli%20leaders%20%E2%80%93%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.haaretz.com%2Fisrael-news%2F2023-10-20%2Fty-article-opinion%2F.premium%2Fa-brief-history-of-the-netanyahu-hamas-alliance%2F0000018b-47d9-d242-abef-57ff1be90000%5C%22%3Eespecially%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20had%20continued%20to%20intermittently%20back%20the%20Islamist%20terror%20group%20to%20cynically%20further%20their%20selfish%20political%20ends%20to%20retain%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20media%20outlets%2C%20including%20the%20%3Cem%3EWashington%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20have%20convincingly%20argued%20in%20recent%20years%20that%20Hamas%20was%20in%20reality%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20Taliban%2C%20patronised%20by%20Tel%20Aviv%20in%20the%20age-old%20colonial%20strategy%20of%20divide-and-rule%20for%20its%20own%20complex%20and%20twisted%20cynical%20ends.%20But%20in%20classic%20blowback%20follow-through%2C%20Hamas%2C%20under%20Tel%20Aviv%E2%80%99s%20patronage%2C%20mutated%20into%20a%20deadly%2C%20cunning%20and%20implacable%20foe%20for%20its%20sponsor%2C%20its%20ferocity%20culminating%20in%20last%20month%E2%80%99s%20well-planned%20hit%20in%20which%20it%20killed%20around%201%2C400%20Israelis%20and%20took%20240%20others%20hostage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnalysts%20said%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20prior%20backing%20of%20Hamas%20was%20prompted%20by%20its%20attempt%20to%20%E2%80%98manage%E2%80%99%20Tel%20Aviv%E2%80%99s%20immediate%20point%20of%20Palestinian%20pain%2C%20which%20for%20the%20newly%20founded%20Jewish%20nation%2C%20was%20personified%20in%20its%20early%20years%20of%20existence%20by%20Yasser%20Arafat%E2%80%99s%20secular%20and%20left-leaning%20Fatah%20party.%20Fatah%20%E2%80%93%20meaning%20victory%20%E2%80%93%20comprised%20the%20core%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20Liberation%20Organisation%20(PLO)%20founded%20in%201964%20to%20fight%20for%20a%20homeland%2C%2016%20years%20after%20its%20people%20were%20arbitrarily%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Ftrapped-in-indefinite-exile-the-history-of-palestinian-refugees-over-last-seven-decades%5C%22%3Erendered%20homeless%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20though%20a%20terrorist%20organisation%20for%20Israel%2C%20the%20PLO%20was%20recognised%20by%20neighbouring%20Arab%20states%20as%20well%20as%20India%20%E2%80%93%20the%20first%20non-Arab%20country%20to%20acknowledge%20it%20as%20the%20sole%20and%20legitimate%20representative%20of%20dispossessed%20Palestinians.%20Arafat%2C%20with%20his%20distinctive%20black%20and%20white%20chequered%20keffiyeh%20headdress%20and%20holstered%20pistol%20at%20his%20hip%2C%20visited%20India%20periodically.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F08175434%2FQalandiya_Checkpoint.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F08175434%2FQalandiya_Checkpoint.jpg%20960w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F08175434%2FQalandiya_Checkpoint-300x200.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-684151%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22640%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20mural%20of%20Yasser%20Arafat.%20Photo%3A%20Anthony%20Baratier%2FWikimedia%20Commons%2C%20CC%20BY-SA%203.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsequently%2C%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20military%20and%20security%20establishment%2C%20facing%20an%20existential%20crisis%2C%20needed%20to%20offset%20the%20PLO%20with%20one%20of%20its%20own%20kind%20and%20Hamas%20%E2%80%93%20an%20acronym%20for%20Harakat%20al-Muqawamah%20al-Isamiyya%20or%20Islamic%20Resistance%20Movement%20%E2%80%93%20ideally%20fitted%20the%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAffiliated%20with%20Egypt%E2%80%99s%20proscribed%20Muslim%20Brotherhood%2C%20the%20Sunni-Palestinian%20Hamas%20group%20was%20founded%20in%20Gaza%20in%201973%20as%20an%20Islamist%20charity%20organisation%20called%20Mujama-al-Islamiya%2C%20by%20Ahmed%20Yassin%2C%20a%20near-blind%20and%20quadriplegic%20Imam%20and%20activist.%20In%20his%20proselytising%20endeavours%2C%20Yassin%20soon%20found%20an%20unexpected%20ally%20in%20Israel%2C%20which%20at%20the%20time%20controlled%20Gaza%2C%20having%20captured%20it%20from%20Egypt%20after%20the%20six-day%20war%20in%201967%2C%20and%20under%20Tel%20Aviv%E2%80%99s%20patronage%2C%20he%20set%20about%20establishing%20a%20network%20of%20kindergartens%2C%20schools%2C%20clinics%2C%20blood%20banks%2C%20daycare%20centres%2C%20youth%20groups%20and%20even%20an%20Islamic%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Palestinian%20imam%20was%20further%20emboldened%20by%20Israel%20loosening%20previous%20restrictions%20on%20activists%20promoting%20political%20Islam%20in%20Gaza%2C%20and%20thus%20proceeded%20to%20officially%20register%20his%20Mujama%20al-Isamiya%20first%20as%20a%20charity%20and%20later%2C%20once%20again%20with%20Tel%20Aviv%E2%80%99s%20backing%2C%20elevated%20its%20status%20to%20that%20of%20an%20association.%20Mujama%20members%20were%20also%20permitted%20by%20Israel%20to%20disseminate%20their%20message%20in%20occupied%20Gaza%20to%20build%20%E2%80%98goodwill%E2%80%99%20amongst%20local%20Palestinians.%20Subsequently%2C%20this%20eventually%20assisted%20Hamas%20in%20acquiring%20political%20legitimacy%2C%20by%20securing%20control%20of%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20in%202007%2C%20following%20elections%20that%20took%20place%20after%20the%202005%20Israeli%20pull-out%20from%20the%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsrael%2C%20for%20its%20part%2C%20then%20fully%20engaged%20in%20battling%20the%20PLO%2C%20stood%20back%20when%20its%20%E2%80%98collaborator%E2%80%99%20Islamist%20group%20inevitably%20clashed%20with%20and%20combated%20its%20rival%20Fatah%20Palestinian%20secularists.%20In%20this%20region%2C%20a%20%E2%80%98collaborator%E2%80%99%20from%20either%20the%20Jewish%20or%20Muslim%20communities%20co-operating%20with%20the%20other%20side%2C%20is%20regarded%20as%20the%20ultimate%20traitor.%20Even%20mere%20suspicion%2C%20in%20many%20cases%2C%20of%20collaborating%20with%20%E2%80%98the%20other%E2%80%99%2C%20was%20enough%20to%20hopelessly%20damn%20the%20concerned%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESteady%20Israeli%20funding%20to%20Mujama%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20augmented%20its%20influence%20and%20reach%20and%20having%20attained%20financial%20solvency%20alongside%20military%20organisation%2C%20it%20ended%20up%20morphing%20into%20Hamas%20in%201987-88%2C%20following%20the%20outbreak%20of%20the%20First%20of%20three%20Intifadas%20or%20rebellions%20by%20Palestinians%20against%20their%20Israeli%20occupiers.%20However%2C%20soon%20after%2C%20the%20fledgling%20Hamas%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98sponsorship%E2%80%99%20ties%20with%20Israel%20broke%20down%20as%20its%20founding%20Charter%20or%20Covenant%20refused%20to%20accept%20the%20latter%E2%80%99s%20existence%20and%20vowed%20to%20work%20towards%20its%20total%20elimination.%20Hamas%20also%20categorically%20rejected%20the%20two-state%20solution%20to%20the%20long-running%20conflict%2C%20committing%20itself%20to%20seeking%20an%20Islamic%20Palestinian%20entity%20over%20the%20combined%20territories%20of%20Israel%2C%20the%20West%20Bank%20and%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20through%20a%20concerted%20campaign%20of%20terrorism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20short%2C%20the%20opening%20moves%20of%20what%20was%20steadily%20building%20up%20to%20the%20blowback%20were%20in%20place.%20But%20events%20would%20unravel%20gradually%20and%20bloodily%2C%20as%20they%20normally%20do%20in%20such%20instances%2C%20over%20the%20next%20three%20decades%2C%20in%20which%20Israel%20fought%20three%20wars%20with%20Hamas%20%E2%80%93%20in%202009%2C%202012%20and%202014%20%E2%80%93%20and%20enforced%20a%2017-year-long%20blockade%20of%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20in%20addition%20to%20frequent%20air%20strikes%20and%20targeted%20assassinations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20UK-based%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.analystnews.org%2Fposts%2Fhow-israel-helped-prop-up-hamas-for-decades%5C%22%3EAnalystNews%3C%2Fa%3E%20online%20news%20service%20last%20month%20stated%20that%20%E2%80%98even%20more%20%E2%80%98sinister%E2%80%99%20was%20the%20way%20the%20Israeli%20authorities%20continued%20to%20deliberately%20enable%20Hamas.%20Netanyahu%E2%80%99s%20political%20strategy%2C%20it%20declared%20had%2C%20since%202009%20revolved%20around%20keeping%20Hamas%20alive%20and%20kicking%2C%20even%20if%20it%20hurts%20Israelis.%20%E2%80%9CWhile%20Israel%20and%20Netanyahu%20give%20lip%20service%20to%20seeking%20a%20two-state%20solution%2C%20Hamas%20provides%20(it)%20a%20convenient%20excuse%20to%20avoid%20pursuing%20one%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20news%20portal%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20day%20after%20the%20October%207%20attack%2C%20the%20conservative%20Jerusalem-based%20%3Cem%3ETimes%20of%20Israel%3C%2Fem%3E%20online%20newspaper%20went%20even%20further%20via%20an%20op-ed%20piece%20entitled%3A%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.timesofisrael.com%2Ffor-years-netanyahu-propped-up-hamas-now-its-blown-up-in-our-faces%2F%5C%22%3EFor%20years%2C%20Netanyahu%20propped%20up%20Hamas.%20Now%20it%E2%80%99s%20blown%20up%20in%20our%20faces.%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%98%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F18123957%2FF8aEEn1WYAAtWt0.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F18123957%2FF8aEEn1WYAAtWt0.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F18123957%2FF8aEEn1WYAAtWt0-300x159.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F18123957%2FF8aEEn1WYAAtWt0-1024x544.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-680601%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22637%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIsrael%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu.%20Photo%3A%20X%2F%40netanyahu%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAuthored%20by%20the%20newspaper%E2%80%99s%20political%20correspondent%20Tal%20Schneider%2C%20the%20commentary%20stated%20that%20for%20years%2C%20various%20governments%20led%20by%20Netanyahu%20had%20pursued%20an%20approach%20that%20divided%20power%20between%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20and%20the%20West%20Bank%20%E2%80%93%20bringing%20Palestinian%20Authority%20(PA)%20president%20Mahmoud%20Abbas%20to%20his%20knees%20%E2%80%93%20while%20initiating%20moves%20that%20propped%20up%20Hamas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%2C%20Schneider%20stated%2C%20was%20to%20prevent%20Abbas%20%E2%80%93%20or%20anyone%20else%20in%20the%20PA%E2%80%99s%20(feeble)%20West%20Bank%20government%20%E2%80%93%20from%20advancing%20toward%20the%20establishment%20of%20a%20Palestinian%20state.%20Amid%20this%20bid%20to%20impair%20Abbas%2C%20Hamas%20had%20been%20upgraded%20from%20a%20mere%20terror%20group%20to%20an%20organisation%20with%20which%20Israel%20held%20indirect%20negotiations%20via%20Egypt%2C%20and%20one%20that%20was%20allowed%20to%20receive%20infusions%20of%20cash%20from%20abroad%2C%20Schneider%20wrote.%20Most%20of%20the%20time%2C%20she%20added%2C%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20policy%20was%20to%20treat%20the%20PA%20as%20a%20burden%20and%20Hamas%20as%20an%20asset.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20in%202021%2C%20Brigadier%20General%20Yitzhak%20Segev%2C%20Gaza%20governor%20in%20the%20early%201980s%2C%20had%20told%20the%20%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20he%20had%20helped%20finance%20Hamas%20as%20a%20counterweight%20to%20the%20secularists%20and%20Leftists%20of%20the%20PLO%20and%20the%20Fatah%20Party%20led%20by%20Arafat.%20He%20admitted%20to%20funding%20Hamas%20himself%20with%20Israeli%20taxpayer%20money%20that%20was%20later%20used%20to%20kill%20the%20same%20people%20who%20were%20funding%20them%2C%20revealing%20thereby%20the%20copybook%20rollout%20of%20the%20classic%20blowback%20syndrome.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20corroborated%20further%20by%20David%20Remick%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newyorker.com%2Fmagazine%2F2023%2F11%2F06%2Fisrael-gaza-war-hamas%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ENew%20Yorker%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20late%20October%2C%20when%20he%20quoted%20Netanyahu%20telling%20his%20Likud%20Party%20supporters%20at%20a%20closed-door%20meeting%20in%202019%20that%20anyone%20who%20wanted%20to%20thwart%20the%20establishment%20of%20a%20Palestinian%20state%20must%20support%20bolstering%20Hamas%20and%20transferring%20money%20to%20Hamas.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20part%20of%20our%20strategy%20%E2%80%93%20to%20isolate%20the%20Palestinians%20in%20Gaza%20from%20the%20Palestinians%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20Israeli%20PM%20had%20added%2C%20according%20to%20Remick.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20yet%20again%2C%20to%20further%20drive%20home%20the%20same%20point%2C%20Israeli%20general-turned-academic-researcher%20Gershon%20Hacohen%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fcommentisfree%2F2023%2Fnov%2F05%2Fin-middle-east-as-in-greek-tragedy-justice-must-prevail-over-moral-absolutism%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20in%20order%20to%20prevent%20the%20two-state%20option%2C%20Netanyahu%20was%20%E2%80%98turning%20Hamas%20into%20his%20closest%20partner%E2%80%99.%20The%20former%20two-star%20Israeli%20Defence%20Forces%20officer%20said%20Hamas%20was%20an%20enemy%2C%20but%20covertly%20it%20was%20a%20(Netanyahu)%20ally.%20He%20further%20added%20that%20Israel%20was%20wreaking%20devastation%20in%20Gaza%20in%20pursuit%20of%20a%20monster%20it%20helped%20spawn.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20short%2C%20the%20blowback%20in%20Gaza%20and%20Israel%20has%20just%20begun%20unravelling%20and%20its%20consequences%20%E2%80%93%20inadvertent%20or%20intended%20%E2%80%93%20augur%20another%20%3Cem%3ENakba%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20catastrophe%20for%20the%20Palestinians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699582578000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F12135727%2FParade_of_Palestinian_Mujahideen_12.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fas-palestinians-confront-a-second-nakba-the-relationship-between-israel-and-hamas-is-complicated%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Netanyahu's%20goal%20is%20to%20prevent%20the%20two-state%20solution%20at%20any%20cost.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fas-palestinians-confront-a-second-nakba-the-relationship-between-israel-and-hamas-is-complicated%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22New%20island%20is%20born%20in%20Japan%20after%20undersea%20volcanic%20eruption%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699581887000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105108163%2Cimgsize-98018.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fnew-island-is-born-in-japan-after-undersea-volcanic-eruption%2Farticleshow%2F105108161.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F105108161.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EA%20new%20island%20has%20emerged%20near%20Japan's%20Ogasawara%20island%20chain%20after%20an%20undersea%20volcano%20erupted%20in%20October%202023.%20The%20island%2C%20about%20100%20meters%20in%20diameter%2C%20was%20formed%20by%20phreatomagmatic%20eruptions.%20This%20is%20not%20the%20first%20time%20such%20an%20event%20has%20occurred%20in%20the%20area%2C%20as%20the%20Ogasawara%20island%20chain%20is%20a%20volcanic%20arc%20consisting%20of%20over%2030%20islands.%20However%2C%20the%20new%20island%20may%20not%20last%20long%20due%2