0city%20rats%20might%20not%20go%20after%20wildlife%20in%20the%20same%20numbers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20if%20all%20rats%20in%20NYC%20died%20tomorrow%20it%20would%20still%20save%20a%20lot%20of%20animals%20like%20birds%2C%20coyotes%2C%20foxes%2C%20and%20feral%20cats%20that%20die%20each%20year%20from%20rodenticide%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnyc-hiring-bloodthirsty-director-rodent-mitigation-fight-rats-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epoison%20used%20to%20kill%20rats%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Munshi-South%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EByers%20agreed%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20big%20problems%20is%20that%20the%20poison%20just%20doesn't%20stay%20in%20the%20rats%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20ends%20up%20in%20the%20animals%20that%20feed%20on%20the%20rats%2C%20like%20the%20predatory%20birds%20or%20other%20urban%20wildlife%20that%20eat%20those%20animals.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20rat%20leaves%20its%20burrow%20in%20a%20park%20in%20New%20York%20City%20in%202015.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6408d95d1bbdd30018ed7c09%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20rat%20leaves%20its%20burrow%20in%20a%20park%20in%20New%20York%20City%2C%20possibly%20to%20go%20hunt%20down%20some%20fresh%20garbage.%3Cp%3EMary%20Altaffer%2FAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20scavengers%2C%20rats%20likely%20play%20some%20role%20in%20helping%20remove%20garbage%20from%20city%20streets%20and%20distributing%20seeds%2C%20Byers%20said.%20But%20Munshi-South%20countered%20that%20and%20said%20ants%20and%20other%20animals%20could%20fill%20the%20role%20of%20removing%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20positive%20impact%20would%20likely%20be%20on%20people%20experiencing%20homelessness%20or%20those%20who%20live%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-bought-rat-infeste