e%2Fcar-free-reduce-carbon-footprint-cost-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexhaust%20released%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20200%20cars%2C%20the%20Times%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20current%20operations%20are%20relatively%20small%2C%20but%20the%20company%20has%20plans%20to%20expand.%20Shashank%20Samala%20told%20the%20Times%20that%20they%20want%20to%20get%20to%20millions%20of%20tons%20per%20year%20by%20building%20more%20factories%20like%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EGrabbing%20carbon%20like%20a%20sponge%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228640%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20looks%20up%2C%20off%20screen%2C%20with%20sheets%20in%20the%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654d436a36d588dc55ce18fc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225760%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EShashank%20Samala%2C%20co-founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Heirloom%20Carbon%2C%20at%20the%20company%20headquarters%20in%20Brisbane%2C%20California.%3Cp%3EJENN%20CAIN%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHeirloom%20uses%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-government-launches-largest-ever-carbon-removal-initiative-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edirect%20air%20capture%20technology%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20essentially%20means%20that%20its%20product%20is%20able%20to%20suck%20free%20carbon%20dioxide%20out%20of%20the%20air%2C%20according%20to%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.heirloomcarbon.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewebsite%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20does%20this%20by%20%26quot%3Busing%20limestone%20like%20a%20sponge.%26quot%3B%20The%20facility%20processes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-limestone-kilns-are-slowly-killing-entire-families-in-pakistan%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elimestone%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20removing%20the%20carbon%20dioxide%20from%20it%2C%20which%20turns%20it%20into%20a%20fine%20white%20powder%2C%20called%20calcium%20oxide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWater%20is%20then%20added%20to%20the%20calcium%20oxide%2C%20and%20the%20resulting%20mixture%20is%20spread%20out%20on%20metal%20trays%20exposed%20to%20the%20open%20air%2C%20where%20it%20absorbs%20carbon%20dioxide%20from%20the%20atmosphere%20and%20turns%20back%20into%20limestone%2C%20per%20the%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20facility%20can%20then%20use%20the%20limestone%20it%20just%20produced%20to%20start%20the%20process%20again%2C%20%26quot%3Blike%20repeatedly%20wringing%20a%20sponge%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20Heirloom's%20website.%20The%20captured%20carbon%20dioxide%20gets%20packed%20into%20concrete%20or%20injected%20into%20the%20ground%2C%20where%20Heirloom%20said%20it's%20held%20permanently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20whole%20process%20is%20powered%20by%20renewable%20energy%2C%20and%20the%20company%20has%20publicly%20pledged%20to%20not%20accept%20investments%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fexxon-buying-denbury-carbon-capture-business-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoil%20and%20gas%20companies%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20NYT%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhy%20they%20made%20this%20tech%20in%20the%20first%20place%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EExcess%20carbon%20dioxide%20in%20the%20atmosphere%20traps%20heat%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcarbon-dioxide-removal-air-sky-machine-climate-change-climeworks-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewarms%20the%20planet%3C%2Fa%3E.%20If%20we%20keep%20adding%20carbon%20dioxide%20into%20the%20atmosphere%2C%20experts%20say%20we're%20headed%20to%20a%20future%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclimate-change-sea-level-rise-roads-highways-economy-solutions-resiliency-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigher%20sea%20levels%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flahaina-maui-wildfire-what-went-wrong-climate-colonialism-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efrequent%20natural%20disasters%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20fewer%20healthy%20human%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20recent%20report%20from%20the%20World%20Wildlife%20Fund%20and%20%3Cspan%3EBoston%20Consulting%20Group%20%3C%2Fspan%3Efound%20that%20if%20we%20continue%20using%20fossil%20fuels%20at%20current%20rates%2C%20there'll%20be%20the%20equivalent%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgreen-energy-transition-saves-millions-years-healthy-human-life-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E211%20million%20years%20of%20human%20life%20lost%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20lived%20with%20disability%20in%20the%20year%202050%2C%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20it's%20crucial%20to%20reduce%20the%20amount%20of%20greenhouse%20gasses%20we're%20releasing.%20By%20removing%20some%20of%20the%20carbon%20dioxide%20we've%20already%20released%2C%20it%20could%20help%20us%20halt%20climate%20change%20even%20sooner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20science%20is%20clear%3A%20Cutting%20back%20carbon%20emissions%20through%20renewable%20energy%20alone%20won't%20stop%20the%20damage%20from%20climate%20change%2C%26quot%3B%20Secretary%20of%20Energy%20Jennifer%20Granholm%2C%20told%20the%20Times.%20%26quot%3BDirect%20air%20capture%20technology%20is%20a%20game-changing%20tool%20that%20gives%20us%20a%20shot%20at%20removing%20the%20carbon%20pollution.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ECarbon%20capture%20is%20not%20a%20cure%20for%20climate%20change%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUsing%20carbon%20capture%20alone%20won't%20be%20a%20cure-all%20for%20our%20climate%20woes.%20To%20avoid%20a%20hotter%20future%2C%20we%20need%20to%20rapidly%20reduce%20our%20dependence%20on%20fossil%20fuels%2C%20according%20to%20the%20WWF%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20some%20experts%20are%20wary%20of%20carbon%20capture%2C%20like%20climate%20scientist%20Peter%20Kalmus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKalmus%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcarbon-capture-storage-expensive-climate-change-2021-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20Insider%20in%202021%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20pollutive%20companies%20might%20promote%20investments%20in%20carbon%20capture%20to%20distract%20the%20public%20from%20the%20amount%20of%20fossil%20fuels%20they're%20actively%20releasing%20into%20the%20air.%20This%20mirrors%20a%20popular%20sentiment%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffund-carbon-removal-corporates-avoid-bad-credits-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecarbon%20offsets%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFossil-fuel%20companies%20love%20carbon%20capture%20because%20it%20really%20does%20let%20them%20off%20the%20hook%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-first-commercial-carbon-capture-facility-opens-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699566146000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654d468cb788914e555399d4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-first-commercial-carbon-capture-facility-opens-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Heirloom%20Carbon%20Technologies%20launched%20the%20first%20US%20plant%20for%20carbon%20capture%2C%20potentially%20helping%20stave%20off%20climate%20change.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Maiya%20Focht)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A34%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-first-commercial-carbon-capture-facility-opens-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%2030-year%20Treasury%20yield%20sharply%20rebounds%20amid%20sagging%20demand%20in%20latest%20government%20bond%20auction%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225251%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20US%20Treasury%20payment%20check.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654d35e336d588dc55ce0bcb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222625%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20US%20Treasury%20payment%20check.%3Cp%3EDouglas%20Sacha%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%2030-year%20Treasury%20yield%20surged%20to%20a%20peak%20of%20over%204.80%25%20on%20Thursday.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20move%20higher%20in%20yields%20comes%20after%20the%20recent%20auction%20was%20met%20with%20considerably%20weak%20demand.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EDealers%20picked%20up%20over%2024%25%20of%20the%20issued%20asset%2C%20well%20above%20the%20average%2011%25.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2030-year%20Treasury%20yield%20rose%20steeply%20on%20Thursday%2C%20spiking%20by%20as%20much%20as%2015%20basis%20points%20and%20rising%20back%20towards%20recent%20highs%20after%20steadily%20retreating%20in%20recent%20weeks.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20rate%20settled%20at%20slightly%20lower%20levels%2C%20it%20peaked%20at%20over%204.80%25%20in%20Thursday's%20session.%20The%20surge%20was%20accompanied%20by%20a%20similar%20upside%20in%20the%2010-year%20Treasury%20note%2C%20which%20jumped%20as%20much%20as%2011%20basis%20points.%20Yields%20were%20also%20pushed%20up%20during%20the%20session%20by%20hawkish%20comments%20from%20Federal%20Reserve%20Chair%20Jerome%20Powell%2C%20who%20said%20on%20a%20panel%20that%20the%20central%20bank%20was%20not%20convinced%20it%20had%20done%20enough%20to%20combat%20high%20inflation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20resurgence%20in%20yields%20was%20the%20immediate%20aftermath%20of%20a%20disappointing%20auction%20on%20Thursday.%20Stats%20from%20the%20Treasury%20show%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftreasurydirect.gov%2Finstit%2Fannceresult%2Fpress%2Fpreanre%2F2023%2FR_20231109_3.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprimary%20dealers%20forced%20to%20pick%20up%20around%2024.7%25%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20the%20issuance%20in%20the%20latest%20%2424%20billion%20sale%20of%2030-year%20bonds.%20That's%20well%20above%20the%20average%2011%25%20that%20banks%20tend%20to%20purchase%20when%20investors%20retreat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWeak%20demand%20was%20also%20made%20apparent%20by%20the%20bid-to-cover%20ratio%2C%20which%20measures%20the%20gap%20between%20the%20dollar%20value%20of%20bids%20received%20and%20the%20amount%20sold.%20In%20Thursday's%20auction%2C%20the%20metric%20neared%20its%20lowest%20level%20in%20almost%20two%20years%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftradingeconomics.com%2Funited-states%2Fgovernment-bond-yield%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETrading%20Economics%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0Added%20to%20that%2C%20the%20auction%20also%20saw%20the%20smallest%20pool%20of%20bidders%20since%202021.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fbonds%2Ftreasury-bond-auction-us-debt-crisis-fed-buying-quantitative-tightening-2023-10%5C%22%3ENew%20government%20bond%20issuance%20last%20month%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20already%20seeing%20softer%20demand%2C%20though%20bond%20traders%20were%20recently%20encouraged%20by%20the%20Treasury%20Department's%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffinance.yahoo.com%2Fnews%2Fready-more-us-debt-sticker-204501804.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurprise%20decision%20to%20limit%20the%20sale%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20long-dated%20US%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20slowdown%20isn't%20enough%20to%20reverse%20ongoing%20concerns%20in%20the%20bond%20market%2C%20which%20fueled%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fbonds%2Ftreasury-bond-yields-market-selloff-market-crashes-dot-com-bubble-2023-10%5C%22%3Ehistoric%20sell-off%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Treasurys%20last%20quarter.%20That's%20as%20traders%20are%20less%20eager%20to%20pick%20up%20debt%20amid%20increasing%20federal%20deficits%2C%20and%20are%20demanding%20higher%20compensation%20to%20take%20on%20the%20massive%20oversupply%20of%20Treasurys.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20u