1668%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDonald%20Trump%20attends%20his%20New%20York%20civil%20fraud%20trial.%3Cp%3EPool%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20judge%20on%20Thursday%20rejected%20Trump's%20bid%20for%20an%20early%20win%20in%20his%20civil%20fraud%20trial%20in%20New%20York.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20decision%20was%20preceded%20by%20often%20colorful%20arguments%20invoking%20Putin%2C%20geese%2C%20and%C2%A0%26quot%3Bspaghetti%20night.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20defense%20will%20now%20begin%20an%20expected%206-week%20case%2C%20fighting%20NY's%20efforts%20to%20penalize%20Trump%20more%20than%20%24250M.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EDonald%20Trump%20lost%20his%20bid%20for%20an%20early%20win%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrumps-ny-fraud-trial-opens-today-heres-why-still-matters-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20his%20New%20York%20fraud%20trial%20%3C%2Fa%3EThursday%2C%20after%20three%20hours%20of%20sometimes%20colorful%20legal%20arguments%20%E2%80%94%20in%20which%20lawyers%20and%20the%20judge%20invoked%20the%20president%20of%20Russia%2C%20geese%20of%20either%20gender%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bspaghetti%20night.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BVladimir%20Putin%20has%20some%20openings%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20lawyer%20Christopher%20Kise%20sniped%20at%20a%20lawyer%20for%20New%20York%20at%20one%20point%20mid-morning%2C%20in%20complaining%20about%20a%20state%20effort%20to%20bar%20defense%20expert%20witnesses%20from%20testifying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20it's%20totally%20uncalled%20for.%20Totally%20incorrect%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judge%20quickly%20told%20Kise%20of%20his%20Putin%20crack.%20Kise%20immediately%20promised%20to%20%26quot%3Brefrain%20from%20further%20pejoratives%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20later%20apologized.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20presiding%20over%20the%20non-jury%20trial%2C%20state%20Supreme%20Court%20Justice%20Arthur%20Engoron%2C%20did%20not%20issue%20a%20formal%20ruling%20on%20Trump's%20request%20to%20stop%20the%20trial%20and%20declare%20the%20former%20president%20the%20winner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20the%20judge%20repeated%20what%20he's%20said%20in%20earlier%20rulings%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-new-york-judge-finds-business-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethat%20there%20is%20already%20plentiful%20proof%20of%20fraud%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20he%20told%20both%20sides%20to%20prepare%20to%20resume%20trial%20next%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20trial%20is%20now%20scheduled%20to%20continue%20into%20mid-December%2C%20with%20a%20100-witness-long%20parade%20of%20Trump%20witnesses%20queuing%20up%20to%20testify%2C%20starting%20Monday%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-jr-learns-ny-wants-even-higher-fraud-penalties-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20reprise%20appearance%20by%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20Jr.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20use%20a%20%26quot%3BGroundhog's%20Day%26quot%3B%20analogy%20%E2%80%94%20apt%20given%20the%20often%20repetitive%20testimony%20and%20arguments%20so%20far%20%E2%80%94%20the%20judge%20on%20Thursday%20emerged%20from%20his%20chambers%20after%20the%20lunch%20break%20and%20appeared%20to%20declare%20around%20six%20more%20weeks%20of%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20wild%20and%20crazy%20hearing%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20actual%20Trumps%20were%20present%20in%20the%20Manhattan%20courtroom%20to%20hear%20the%20bad%20news.%20Instead%2C%20there%20were%20two%20tables%20full%20of%20lawyers%2C%20both%20for%20the%20defense%20and%20for%20state%20Attorney%20General%20Letitia%20James.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJames%20alleges%20the%20former%20president%2C%20his%20two%20sons%2C%20and%20his%20New%20York-headquartered%20golf-resort%20and%20real-estate%20empire%2C%20the%20Trump%20Organization%2C%20routinely%20lied%20in%20a%20decade's%20worth%20of%20banking%20documents.%20The%20lies%20helped%20Trump%20win%20more%20than%20%24250%20million%20in%20ill-gotten%20profits%20and%20loan%20interest-rate%20discounts%2C%20the%20AG%20alleges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20documents%20case%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20of%20James'%20lead%20lawyers%2C%20Kevin%20C.%20Wallace%2C%20said%20during%20the%20free-wheeling%20arguments%20that%20preceded%20the%20judge%20telling%20everyone%20to%20keep%20going.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20documents%20are%20Trump's%20annual%2C%2030-page%20assertions%20of%20net%20worth%2C%20the%20so-called%20%26quot%3Bstatements%20of%20financial%20condition%26quot%3B%20that%20are%20central%20to%20the%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20president%20used%20these%20net-worth%20estimates%20to%20secure%20and%20maintain%20the%20more%20than%20%24400%20million%20in%20development%20loans%20behind%20his%20Chicago%20skyscraper%2C%20his%20Miami%20golf%20course%2C%20and%20the%20Trump%20International%20Hotel%20in%20the%20historic%20Old%20Post%20Office%20building%20in%20Washington%2C%20D.C.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20self-reported%20worth%20in%20these%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-net-worth-math-even-fuzzier-than-ny-last-alleged-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estatements%20of%20financial%20condition%20exceeded%20his%20actual%20worth%20by%20as%20much%20as%20%243.6%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20year%2C%20the%20AG%20has%20alleged.%20The%20three%20Trumps'%20signatures%20are%20on%20multiple%20documents%20affirming%20that%20the%20estimates%20are%20accurate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224096%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22donald%20trump%20new%20york%20civil%20fraud%20attorney%20general%20letitia%20james%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651b21402ce014759e72b37d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222717%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFormer%20president%20Donald%20Trump%20displays%20a%20media%20article%20outside%20the%20courtroom%20at%20the%20New%20York%20State%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20the%20first%20day%20of%20his%20civil%20fraud%20trial.%3Cp%3EKENA%20BETANCUR%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EEnough%20evidence%20to%20fill%20the%20%3Cem%3Eoverflow%3C%2Fem%3E%20courtroom%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWallace%20argued%20that%20these%20net-worth%20statements%20and%20other%20supporting%20documents%2C%20along%20with%20the%20testimony%20from%20the%20past%20five%20weeks%2C%20offer%20ample%20proof%20of%20fraud.%20In%20describing%20how%20ample%2C%20Wallace%20harkened%20back%20to%20an%20exaggeration%20the%20judge%20used%20October%2025%2C%20in%20swatting%20down%20a%20previous%20defense%20request%20for%20an%20early%20verdict%20in%20their%20favor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20enough%20evidence%20to%20fill%20this%20courtroom%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judge%20said%20then.%20Wallace%20took%20the%20analogy%20still%20further%20Thursday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20this%20point%2C%20he%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20a%20courtroom%20one%20floor%20down%2C%20where%20the%20proceedings%20are%20broadcast%20on%20screens%2C%20%26quot%3Bthere's%20enough%20evidence%20to%20fill%20the%20%3Cem%3Eoverflow%3C%2Fem%3E%20courtroom.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKise%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20argued%20that%20having%20a%20lot%20of%20evidence%20isn't%20the%20same%20as%20having%20a%20lot%20of%20good%20evidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESpaghetti%20night%20at%20Manhattan%20Supreme%20Court%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20what%20we%20call%20'spaghetti%20night%2C'%26quot%3B%20Kise%20quipped%20of%20the%20attorney%20general's%20fact-dense%20case%2C%20which%20alleges%20frauds%20involving%20a%20dozen%20Trump%20properties%20and%20a%20half-dozen%20loans%20and%20insurance%20deals%20going%20back%20a%20dozen%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJust%20throw%20it%20against%20the%20wall%20and%20see%20what%20sticks%2C%26quot%3B%20Kise%20complained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20just%20have%20to%20be%20careful%20talking%20about%20spaghetti%20at%20lunchtime%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judge%20quipped%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20wild%20goose%20chase%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%2C%20far%20more%20extended%2C%20food%20analogy%20fluttered%20into%20Thursday's%20pre-lunch%20arguments%20in%20the%20form%20of%20geese%2C%20along%20with%20their%20associated%20condiments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20a%20call-back%20to%20the%20judge%20having%20once%20joked%2C%20back%20in%20October%2C%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-fraud-judge-plucky-retort-michael-cohens-sickbed-tweets-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bwhat's%20sauce%20for%20the%20goose%20is%20sauce%20for%20the%20gander.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20had%20made%20the%20remark%20when%20Kise%20complained%20about%20Michael%20Cohen's%20anti-Trump%20tweets.%20Kise%20reprised%20it%20Thursday%20in%20arguing%20that%20the%20AG%20was%20being%20unfair%20in%20seeking%20to%20bar%20testimony%20by%20defense%20expert%20witnesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20goose-gander%20rule%20applies%20here%2C%20fully%2C%26quot%3B%20Kise%20complained%20of%20the%20AG's%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20reason%20to%20shut%20the%20door%20%26quot%3B%20on%20our%20experts%2C%20Kise%20argued%2C%20%26quot%3Bafter%20they%20have%20benefitted%20handsomely%20from%20it%20being%20open.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Trump%20lawyer%20noted%20that%20none%20of%20the%20state's%20witnesses%2C%20including%20their%20experts%2C%20were%20ever%20barred%20from%20testifying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Amer%2C%20an%20assistant%20attorney%20general%2C%20joined%20in%20promoting%20the%20judge's%20geese-gander%20adage%20to%20%26quot%3Brule%26quot%3B%20status%2C%20though%20he%20disagreed%20with%20Kise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20goose-gander%20rule%20that%20says%20if%20I%20sustain%20ten%20of%20one%20side's%20objections%2C%20I%20have%20to%20sustain%20ten%20of%20the%20other%20side's%20objections%2C%26quot%3B%20Amer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20lunch%2C%20the%20judge%20ruled%20in%20the%20Trump%20team